The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning and neural networks to achieve superhuman performance in games such as chess, shogi, and Go. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of search techniques and evaluation functions, which are topics in game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
